  "prompt": "Is there any management quota at PCCOE Pune? What are the fees?",
  "response": "Yes, Pimpri Chinchwad College of Engineering (PCCOE) in Pune does have a management quota for admissions to its undergraduate and postgraduate programs. The management quota allows students to secure admission based on seats reserved for this category, often with slightly relaxed admission criteria compared to the general merit-based admissions.\n\n### **Management Quota Fees at PCCOE Pune**\nThe fees for the management quota seats are typically higher than the regular fees for merit-based admissions. As of recent information, the approximate fees for management quota seats in the B.Tech program at PCCOE are around **\u20b91.5 lakh to \u20b92 lakh per year**. However, this amount can vary depending on various factors such as the program, institute policies, and updates in the fee structure.\n\n### **Important Notes:**\n1. **Eligibility:** Even for management quota admissions, students must meet the basic eligibility criteria set by the college and the relevant university (e.g., passing 10+2 with PCM for B.Tech).\n2. **Availability:** Seats under the management quota are limited and are subject to availability.\n3. **Direct Inquiry:** For the most accurate and updated fee structure and admission details, it is recommended to directly contact the PCCOE admission office.\n\nIf you\u2019re considering applying through the management quota, ensure you confirm the current fee structure and eligibility criteria directly with the college.",
